Definition.WordDefinition:
Bungee \Bun"gee\, n. 1. (Aeronautics) a spring or other elastic device, especially one attached to a control to facilitate its manipulation. [PJC]
2. same as {bungee cord}. [PJC]
bungee n : an elasticized rope [syn: {bungee cord}]
